cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their localization. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a semi-definite programming algorithm for node localization. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with estimating the positions of sensors in a network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper deals with signal processing and estimation, which are relevant to these fields.
